Step 1: Identify the relevant values.
• Total Current Assets (initial): 20,000,000.00  
• Total Current Assets (end): 20,796,970.06  
• Total Revenue (or Main Business Revenue): 18,062,437.45

Step 2: Calculate the Average Current Assets.
Average Current Assets = (Beginning Current Assets + Ending Current Assets) / 2  
= (20,000,000.00 + 20,796,970.06) / 2  
= 40,796,970.06 / 2  
≈ 20,398,485.03

Step 3: Calculate the Current Assets Turnover Ratio.
Current Assets Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Current Assets  
≈ 18,062,437.45 / 20,398,485.03  
≈ 0.8856

Rounded to two decimal places, the ratio is approximately 0.89.

Thus, the final answer is:
